-PUT on non-existing ancestors returns the wrong code (401)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
When the PUT operation creates a new non-collection resource all ancestors MUST 
already exist. If all ancestors do not exist, the method MUST fail with a 409 
(Conflict) status code. For example, if resource /a/b/c/d.html is to be created 
and /a/b/c/ does not exist, then the request must fail.
http://www.webdav.org/specs/rfc2518.html#rfc.section.8.7.2
In our case (milton API) we will keep going one level up till we find an 
existing resource, in this case root. When found root will run the 
<code>child</code> method without before running the <code>authenticate</code> 
method, resulting in an SC_UNAUTHORIZED return code




-
